			<div class="content">The traditional and accepted _*nix_ way to do this is to use getopt()<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://linux.die.net/man/3/getopt">http://linux.die.net/man/3/getopt</a><!-- m --><br /><br />If you're trying to write portable code in C++ i suggest you take a look at the boost library.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_44_0/doc/html/program_options.html">http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_44_0/do ... tions.html</a><!-- m --></div>

